{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" allows the creation of and interaction with child"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"processes."}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B0C"],"title":"Inherits From","kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP","doc:\/\/GIO\/10GLibObject0B8ProtocolP","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InitableProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SubprocessProtocol"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Subprocess"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Processes can be communicated with using standard GIO-style APIs (ie:","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream"},{"text":"], [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/OutputStream","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]). There are GIO-style APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to wait for process termination (ie: cancellable and with an asynchronous"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variant)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is an API to force a process to terminate, as well as a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"race-free API for sending UNIX signals to a subprocess."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One major advantage that GIO brings over the core GLib library is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"comprehensive API for asynchronous I\/O, such","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.OutputStream.splice_async"},{"type":"text","text":"].  This makes "},{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"significantly more powerful and flexible than equivalent APIs in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"some other languages such as the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"subprocess.py"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"included with Python.  For example, using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"text":" one could","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"create two child processes, reading standard output from the first,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"processing it, and writing to the input stream of the second, all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"without blocking the main loop."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A powerful [method"},{"code":"Gio.Subprocess.communicate","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] API is provided similar to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"communicate()"},{"type":"text","text":" method of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"subprocess.py"},{"text":". This enables very easy","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interaction with a subprocess that has been opened with pipes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"text":" defaults to tight control over the file descriptors open","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the child process, avoiding dangling-FD issues that are caused by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a simple "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()```\/`exec()"},{"type":"text","text":".  The only open file descriptors in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"spawned process are ones that were explicitly specified by the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"text":" API (unless ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_SUBPROCESS_FLAGS_INHERIT_FDS","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" was"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"specified).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"type":"text","text":" will quickly reap all child processes as they exit,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"avoiding ‘zombie processes’ remaining around for long periods of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"time.  [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Subprocess.wait"},{"type":"text","text":"] can be used to wait for this to happen,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but it will happen even without the call being explicitly made."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As a matter of principle, "},{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has no API that accepts"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"shell-style space-separated strings.  It will, however, match the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"typical shell behaviour of searching the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PATH"},{"text":" for executables that do","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not contain a directory separator in their name. By default, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PATH","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the current process is used.  You can specify","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_SUBPROCESS_FLAGS_SEARCH_PATH_FROM_ENVP"},{"text":" to use the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PATH"},{"text":" of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"launcher environment instead.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" attempts to have a very simple API for most uses (ie:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"spawning a subprocess with arguments and support for most typical"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"kinds of input and output redirection).  See [ctor","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Subprocess.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. The","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SubprocessLauncher","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":"] API is provided for more complicated cases","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(advanced types of redirection, environment variable manipulation,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"change of working directory, child setup functions, etc).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A typical use of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"type":"text","text":" will involve calling"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[ctor"},{"code":"Gio.Subprocess.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], followed by [method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Subprocess.wait_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"Gio.Subprocess.wait","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].  After the process exits, the status can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"checked using functions such as [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Subprocess.get_if_exited"},{"type":"text","text":"] (which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"are similar to the familiar ","type":"text"},{"code":"WIFEXITED","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"-style POSIX macros)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that as of GLib 2.82, creating a "},{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" causes the signal","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SIGPIPE"},{"text":" to be ignored for the remainder of the program. If you are writing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a command-line utility that uses "},{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", you may need to take into","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"account the fact that your program will not automatically be killed"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if it tries to write to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stdout"},{"text":" after it has been closed.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SubprocessProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GSubprocess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SubprocessRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSubprocess"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/subprocess"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess"},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Subprocess"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Subprocess","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","title":"Subprocess","externalID":"s:3GIO10SubprocessC","roleHeading":"Class"},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(_:)-295bx","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(_:)-31m8w","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(_:)-6wrri","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(_:)-9hs9e","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(argv:flags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(raw:)-6ab9a","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(raw:)-o0au","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(retainingRaw:)-40ioc","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(retainingRaw:)-5o5d","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Subprocess\/init(subprocess:)"],"generated":true,"title":"Initializers"},{"title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/G